Description. Male (
holotype
).

Habitus as in 
Fig. 1I
. Total length 5.4. Prosoma 1.6 long, 1.5 wide. Diameter of AME 130 µm, ALE 170 µm, PME 150 µm, PLE 160 µm. AME–AME 80 µm, PME–PME 210 µm, PME–ALE 40 µm. Chelicera (
Fig. 2I–J
) with thumb-like proximo-lateral apophysis, conical frontal apophysis and triangular distal apophysis curved dorsally, longer than proximo-lateral apophysis; Opisthosoma 3.6 long, 1.5 wide. Leg Ⅰ 47.3 (11.9 + 0.7 + 12.0 + 20.6 + 2.1), leg II 31.6 (8.8 + 0.6 + 8.0 + 12.8 + 1.4), leg III 20.7 (6.1 + 0.5 + 5.1 + 7.9 + 1.1), leg IV 27.3 (7.9 + 0.6 + 7.0 + 10.9 + 0.9). Ratio of leg Ⅰ (16.1: 1.0: 16.2: 27.8: 2.9), leg II (13.7: 1.0: 12.5: 20.1: 2.3), leg III (11.5: 1.0: 9.6: 14.8: 2.0), leg IV (13.6: 1.0: 12.0: 18.7: 1.6). Leg formula 1243. Tibia Ⅰ L/d 75. Retrolateral trichobothrium on tibia Ⅰ at 6% proximally. Tarsus Ⅰ with 27 pseudosegments. For the other somatic features see description of the species-group above. Palp (
Fig. 11
). Trochanter apophysis (
Fig. 11A–B
) longer than femur, slender, distinctly elongated and slightly curved retrolaterally, with tubercle proximo-retrolaterally; femur ventrally swollen; tibia with prolatero-ventral tubercle; procursus (
Fig. 11B
) brown, slightly sinuated dorsally, with moderate ventral knee; dorso-subdistal portion of procursus slightly swollen, with one short hair and two spines (
Fig. 11C
); procursus tip (
Fig. 11C–E
) with two ridges retrolaterally, pointed projection prolatero-distally (arrowed 
3 in
Fig. 11D
), serrated, distally pointed dorsal process directed prolaterally (arrowed 
1 in
Fig. 11D
), distally hooked membranous prolateral process (arrowed 
2 in
Fig. 11D
), and round ventral process (arrowed in 
Fig. 11E
); genital bulb round, pale yellow; uncus (
Fig. 11F
) dark brown, lingulate, outer proximal margin extended roundly without scales, outer distal margin curved and inner distal margin slightly convex, with many tiny scales; pseudoappendix (
Fig. 11G
) tiny and round; embolus (
Fig. 11G
) pale yellow, slender and distally fringed, weakly sclerotized, about 1.5 times as long as uncus.

Variation.
Males.Prosoma length:1.3–1.9(mean 1.7),tibiaⅠ:10.3–14.9(mean 12.4)(n=10).An intrapopulational variation was observed on the number of serrations on the dorsal process of the procursus tip (
Fig. 15A, D, G, J, M, P
), ranging from prominent to without discernible serrations, as in specimens from Chopyeong 1 tunnel, Jincheon (
Fig. 15M, P
). The length of the dorso-subdistal spines of procursus is also variable.

Females. Prosoma length: 1.3–1.7 (mean 1.5), tibia Ⅰ: 7.7–9.4 (mean 8.4) (n=10). An intrapopulational variation was observed on the shapes of the pore plates of internal genitalia, ranging from ovoid to narrowly oblong (
Fig. 15C, F, I, L, O, R
); specimens from 
holotype
locality (Mt. Chilgapsan, Cheongyang) have ovoid pore plates (
Fig. 15C, F
), but specimens from other localities (Mt. Sureuisan, Eumseong and near Chopyeong 1 tunnel, Jincheon) have narrowly oblong or oblong pore plates (
Fig. 15I, L, O, R
). The epigynal shapes were slightly variable but largely consistent (
Fig. 15B, E, H, K, N, Q
).
